²⁰ The restless ambition of the intellect is one of the Impediments to the attainment of truth. The mind ever desires to penetrate further and further into the nature and causes of things; but in vain. And hence, feeling its helplessness, it falls back upon itself, and supposes the processes of nature to be carried on with the same ends and ln the same manner as the works of man. .

This Aphorism touches on a number of philosophica! difficulties thch it would be impossible within the limits of a work like this to discuss fully or satisfactorily. l shall confine myself toa brief statement of my own opInions and to such references as l think likely to be of real use to the student.
